SUMMARY:⏰ Saturn enters ♈Aries
DESCRIPTION:Saturn enters Aries today for the first time since 1996.\n\nThe last Saturn in Aries transit (1996-1999) opened an era of audacious new ventures — the dot-com explosion\, the founding of Google\, mass internet adoption — and also produced the hubris that eventually crashed them. Saturn in Aries doesn't punish boldness. It tests whether your boldness has bones.\n\nSaturn is the planet of structure\, consequence\, and long-term accountability. Aries is the sign of the self\, the impulse to initiate\, the refusal to wait. Together they ask: what are you actually capable of building from scratch? Not what you dream of starting — what can you sustain?\n\nThe philosopher Seneca said: 'It is not that I'm brave enough to face danger\; it is that I understand what is and isn't worth fearing.' Saturn in Aries is that distinction made concrete. The pioneers who thrive under this transit aren't the most fearless — they're the ones whose courage is attached to something real and considered.\n\nPractically: Saturn in Aries rewards people who begin things — but only if they also finish them. It exposes impatience masquerading as initiative. New ventures started with genuine skill and commitment now have strong foundations. New ventures started on impulse alone will hit walls.\n\nThis transit lasts until 2028. The window you're opening today: What new beginning has been waiting for you to be ready enough to actually commit to it?
CATEGORIES:QUANTUMELODIC,INGRESS
