SUMMARY:🌕 Full Moon ♍Virgo
DESCRIPTION:A Total Lunar Eclipse in Virgo — the Full Moon goes fully dark as Earth's shadow falls across it.\n\nTotal Lunar Eclipses are visible to anyone on the night side of Earth — the Moon doesn't disappear\; it turns deep red (the 'blood moon')\, lit only by all the world's sunrises and sunsets refracted through Earth's atmosphere. You are literally seeing the light of every dawn and dusk on Earth concentrated on one face.\n\nVirgo governs craft\, service\, health\, discernment\, and the daily practices that either support life or slowly undermine it. Lunar eclipses in Virgo tend to surface what has been quietly wrong in the systems and routines we've normalized. The thing that 'isn't a big deal' — except it's been a big deal all along.\n\nThis eclipse opposes the Aquarius eclipse from two weeks ago (Feb 17). Together they form a question: what does it mean to serve the collective (Aquarius) if your own foundation (Virgo) is in disrepair? You cannot give sustainably from depletion. This eclipse makes that undeniable.\n\nVirgo's gift is analysis without paralysis — the ability to look clearly at what is\, without flinching\, and then make precise adjustments. The eclipse accelerates that. Something will be seen tonight that cannot be unseen.\n\nThe Stoic philosophers called this 'the view from above' — seeing your situation with the clarity you'd have if you were looking at someone else's life. That clarity is available tonight. Use it.\n\nWhat have you known\, quietly\, needs to change in your daily life — your health\, your work\, your routines — that you've been managing around rather than addressing?\n\nWhat would actually change if you stopped managing it and started fixing it?
CATEGORIES:QUANTUMELODIC,LUNAR,ECLIPSE
