SUMMARY:🔮 Pluto Retrograde ℞
DESCRIPTION:Pluto stations retrograde today\, beginning approximately five months of apparent backward motion.\n\nPluto moves so slowly that its retrograde periods are less about sudden shifts and more about the difference between external pressure and internal pressure. When Pluto is direct\, transformation tends to feel like something happening to you. When Pluto is retrograde\, it tends to feel like something being demanded of you from within.\n\nPluto governs: the processes of genuine transformation\, what lies beneath the surface\, power dynamics (personal and collective)\, the compulsions that operate beneath conscious choice\, and the necessity of endings as the precondition for regeneration.\n\nPluto currently in Aquarius (since 2023) is doing long-term work on: how power is distributed in societies\, the relationship between technology and human agency\, the transformation of collective structures. During the retrograde\, that same work turns inward — how those same themes operate in your own psychology.\n\nThe psychoanalyst Carl Jung described the 'shadow' as everything we've denied or hidden in order to present an acceptable self. Pluto retrograde is when the shadow has better access to your attention than usual. Not to harm you — to complete you.\n\nWhat do you have power over that you haven't fully claimed?\n\nAnd: what do you maintain power over that would be better released?
CATEGORIES:QUANTUMELODIC,STATION
