SUMMARY:🌿 Chiron enters ♉Taurus
DESCRIPTION:Chiron re-enters Taurus today after a brief return to Aries (it will retrograde back to Aries in September).\n\nChiron in Taurus (first entered 2018) has been surfacing collective wounds around: the body and physical wellbeing\, economic security\, the right to simply exist without justifying it\, the relationship between worth and productivity\, and what it means to belong to the Earth.\n\nThe Chiron wound in Taurus tends to manifest as: chronic tension about money and security that doesn't fully resolve even when circumstances improve\; difficulty with physical self-care or a sense of disconnection from the body\; the feeling that pleasure is somehow not quite deserved\; or a wound around stability — never quite trusting that things won't be taken away.\n\nTaurus is the sign of the senses\, slowness\, embodiment\, and what is genuinely nourishing. Chiron here asks: what does it actually feel like to be in your body\, on this earth\, receiving what life is actually offering — rather than what you fear it might withhold?\n\nThe somatic therapist Peter Levine observes that unresolved trauma lives in the nervous system long after the circumstances that created it have passed. Chiron in Taurus is a years-long invitation to work with exactly that.\n\nWhat does your body know about safety or lack of safety that your thinking mind tends to override?\n\nWhere in your life are you working very hard to feel secure rather than simply allowing yourself to notice that you already are?
