DTEND:20260701T232400Z
SUMMARY:🌟□🌿 Jupiter square Chiron
DESCRIPTION:Jupiter in Leo squares Chiron in Taurus today.\n\nChiron was discovered in 1977 — an anomalous body orbiting between Saturn and Uranus\, neither fully a planet nor a comet. In myth\, Chiron was the centaur teacher-healer who could heal others but not himself — wounded by a poisoned arrow\, he eventually surrendered his immortality to escape the unending pain. In astrology\, Chiron marks the wound that is also the teacher.\n\nJupiter square Chiron is not subtle. Jupiter magnifies\; a square creates pressure. Together they force a confrontation with whatever Chiron represents: the place where you feel fundamentally inadequate\, the story you've carried since early life about your limitations\, the way your wound has paradoxically shaped your gifts.\n\nChiron in Taurus (where it's been since 2018\, and where it remains until June 2026) carries wounds around worth\, material security\, the body\, and the right to simply exist and be enough. Jupiter in Leo is saying: expand\, create\, be seen. Chiron in Taurus is saying: but do you actually believe you deserve to?\n\nThe psychologist Alice Miller observed that many gifted people spend their lives serving a talent rather than living a life — using their gift as the only acceptable justification for existing. That's a Chiron wound\, and this square will surface it.\n\nThe healthy version of this transit: your wound becomes your credential\, not your limitation. The place you suffered most becomes the place you understand most clearly.\n\nWhere do you experience yourself as fundamentally 'not enough' — despite external evidence that might suggest otherwise?\n\nAnd: how might that exact wound be the source of your most genuine usefulness to others?
CATEGORIES:QUANTUMELODIC,ASPECT
UID:6eaf31a0ed57d4207207faf224d02389@quantumelodic.symphony
