SUMMARY:🌊 Neptune Retrograde ℞
DESCRIPTION:Neptune stations retrograde today\, beginning approximately five months of apparent backward motion.\n\nNeptune goes retrograde every year for about five months — it's one of the most regular of the outer planet cycles\, and because Neptune moves so slowly\, its retrograde is less about sudden change and more about a shift in how we perceive.\n\nNeptune direct: the dream is available\, the imagination is active\, the boundaries between self and other are permeable. Sometimes productively. Sometimes dangerously.\n\nNeptune retrograde: the dissolving quality turns inward. This can produce clearer perception of external reality — the fog lifts somewhat\, and things that seemed confusing become clearer. It can also produce a deeper access to the interior life — dreams may be more vivid\, creative work may go deeper\, and spiritual practice (if you have one) may feel more genuine.\n\nNeptune in Aries (new territory for Neptune) retrograding means: the idealism and visionary energy of this transit turns inward for review. What are you actually believing in? What are you projecting onto? What dreams are genuinely yours versus absorbed from the cultural atmosphere?\n\nThe poet Rainer Maria Rilke wrote: 'The only journey is the one within.' Neptune retrograde is that journey's more direct access point.\n\nWhat do you believe — about yourself\, about the world\, about what's possible — that you haven't examined closely enough to know whether it's actually true?\n\nAnd: what would you have to give up believing in order to see something more clearly?
CATEGORIES:QUANTUMELODIC,STATION
