SUMMARY:✨⚹🌿 True Node sextile Chiron
DESCRIPTION:Chiron and the True Node are in aspect today.\n\nThis is a transit about healing as evolution — the specific question of whether your wound is connected to your growth path\, and how.\n\nChiron marks the wound that teaches. The True Node marks the direction of growth. When they aspect each other\, the question is explicit: is the place where you are most vulnerable\, most tender\, or most scarred actually pointing toward your most important development? In myth\, Chiron's wound — the poisoned arrow that could not be removed — became the source of his greatest teaching. He could not heal himself\, but he could heal others. The wound was not eliminated\; it was integrated and transcended.\n\nA square creates friction: the healing path may resist the growth direction\, or you may be using your wound as an excuse to avoid growing. A sextile opens collaboration: the wound is actively pointing toward your evolution. A semi-square is a low-grade irritant that keeps asking to be addressed.\n\nThere's an important nuance here: not all pain is Chiron's. Some wounds are just painful and don't have a hidden gift. Chiron is specifically the wound that is also a portal — but it takes discernment to tell which is which. Today is a good day for that discernment.\n\nToday's sextile: Sextiles are friendly\, productive angles. Unlike trines\, which flow automatically\, sextiles require some activation — they offer opportunity that you have to meet halfway. When you do\, the combination of these two energies tends to produce something neither could create alone.\n\nIs the area of greatest vulnerability or recurring pain in your life pointing you toward something important — or is it simply something that needs to heal?\n\nWhat would it mean to teach from your wound rather than hide it\, protect it\, or be defined entirely by it?
CATEGORIES:QUANTUMELODIC,ASPECT
