SUMMARY:⏰ Saturn Retrograde ℞
DESCRIPTION:Saturn stations retrograde today\, beginning roughly four months of apparent backward motion.\n\nSaturn goes retrograde every year for about 4.5 months — it's one of the most regular of the outer planet retrograde cycles. Unlike Mercury retrograde\, which feels like things getting tangled\, Saturn retrograde feels more like being asked to go back and check your work.\n\nSaturn governs: the structures you've built\, the commitments you've made\, the long-term projects you're accountable to\, and the limits you've accepted or resisted. During Saturn retrograde\, these come up for internal review. The outer circumstances don't necessarily change — but your relationship to them\, your attitude toward the responsibility\, often does.\n\nCommon Saturn retrograde experiences: a project you thought was on track reveals a structural weakness you'd been ignoring. A commitment that felt fine starts to feel like a mismatch. Or conversely: you find your footing on something you'd been procrastinating on\, finally willing to do the harder\, slower version that actually works.\n\nIn Aries (where Saturn currently is)\, the retrograde specifically reviews: where you've been bold without being prepared\, or prepared without being bold. The gap between intention and follow-through becomes very visible.\n\nWhat structure in your life — a project\, a commitment\, a role — have you been maintaining out of inertia rather than genuine alignment?\n\nAnd: what would it look like to recommit to it properly\, or to end it properly\, rather than just continuing to manage it from the side?
CATEGORIES:QUANTUMELODIC,STATION
