DTEND:20260812T143600Z
SUMMARY:🌑 New Moon ♌Leo
DESCRIPTION:A Total Solar Eclipse in Leo — totality\, complete darkness at midday.\n\nTotal Solar Eclipses are among the rarest experiences a human can witness. In the path of totality\, day becomes night for a few minutes. Stars appear. The corona — the Sun's outer atmosphere\, normally invisible — surrounds the darkness in silver light. Animals go quiet. People weep\, unexpectedly.\n\nEvery culture in history has treated Solar Eclipses as turning points. Not because of superstition\, but because they are disorienting in a way that strips the ordinary and makes the scale of things visible. You are watching the Moon — a rock 384\,000 km away — fit precisely over the Sun\, which is 150 million km away\, because of a coincidence of relative sizes that won't hold forever. The Moon is slowly moving away from Earth. In geological time\, total solar eclipses are a temporary phenomenon. We live in the narrow window when they're possible.\n\nLeo governs creative expression\, the individual self\, courage\, and the authentic life — the life you would actually choose rather than the life circumstances assigned you. A Solar Eclipse in Leo resets identity. Something in how you understand yourself is permanently altered around this date.\n\nThis eclipse is part of the Saros Series 155 — a cycle of eclipses separated by 18 years. Look back at August 2008 and August 1990. What was being seeded in your life during those windows? The thread continues today.\n\nThe psychologist James Hollis writes: 'The larger life is not the easier life.' Solar Eclipses in Leo tend to make that choice visible. The smaller\, safer version of your life is an option. So is the larger one.\n\nWhat do you know\, in the part of you that doesn't negotiate with fear\, that you are actually here to do or be?\n\nWhat would you begin today if you believed you had permission?
CATEGORIES:QUANTUMELODIC,LUNAR,ECLIPSE
