SUMMARY:🌕 Full Moon ♓Pisces
DESCRIPTION:A Partial Lunar Eclipse in Pisces — Earth's shadow falls across part of the Moon.\n\nPisces governs: the unconscious\, spirituality\, compassion\, dissolution\, creativity\, and the places where individual identity softens into something larger. It is the last sign — the sign that contains all the others. Its shadow side is escapism\, confusion\, and the places we go to not feel what we feel.\n\nA Lunar Eclipse in Pisces tends to surface what we've been avoiding through softness — not avoidance through distraction\, but avoidance through blurring. The drink that takes the edge off. The spiritual practice that becomes spiritual bypassing. The compassion extended endlessly outward to avoid looking inward.\n\nThis eclipse completes a cycle that began with the Leo Solar Eclipse two weeks ago. Leo asks: who are you as an individual? What do you genuinely want?\nPisces answers: but you are also part of something much larger. The tension between those two truths is what this eclipse makes visible.\n\nCarl Jung wrote: 'The privilege of a lifetime is to become who you truly are.' Pisces eclipses ask the harder version of that: what if becoming who you truly are requires letting go of who you've been — not dramatically\, but like a shoreline that has gradually moved?\n\nWhat are you carrying that belongs to someone else? What grief\, obligation\, or identity have you absorbed from others that you've been treating as your own?\n\nWhat would it feel like to put it down — not abandon it\, but simply stop carrying it as if it's yours?
CATEGORIES:QUANTUMELODIC,LUNAR,ECLIPSE
