SUMMARY:⚡ Uranus Retrograde ℞
DESCRIPTION:Uranus stations retrograde today\, beginning roughly five months of apparent backward motion.\n\nUranus is retrograde for about 40% of each year — it's one of the most common of the outer planet retrograde cycles. But its station points (today — the moment it stops and turns) tend to be felt more acutely.\n\nUranus governs: disruption\, sudden change\, the need for liberation\, authentic individuality\, and the impulse to break free from whatever is confining the genuine self. When direct\, Uranus tends to operate through external events — the sudden development\, the unexpected change of plans\, the disruption that arrives from outside. When retrograde\, Uranus operates internally — the restlessness that won't settle\, the authentic self that keeps pushing against the container\, the inner awareness that something needs to change.\n\nThe station point specifically (today) tends to crystallize exactly where you feel most constrained. Not as a comfortable feeling\, necessarily — Uranus stations can feel like a buzzing under the skin\, a nameless agitation. That agitation has information in it.\n\nThe philosopher and psychologist Abraham Maslow identified what he called 'the Jonah complex' — the fear of greatness\, the impulse to pull back from your own potential because expanding into it would require leaving the safety of what's familiar. Uranus retrograde tends to make that pull back toward the authentic self more insistent.\n\nWhere in your life do you feel most constrained — and is that constraint necessary\, or is it something you've been accepting without fully choosing?\n\nWhat would you do\, or be\, or stop doing\, if you genuinely trusted that freedom was available?
CATEGORIES:QUANTUMELODIC,STATION
UID:17a1165f6d4280ff396e13b23b212514@quantumelodic.symphony
