SUMMARY:💕 Venus Retrograde ℞
DESCRIPTION:Venus stations retrograde today — this happens roughly every 18 months\, when Venus (orbiting faster than Earth) laps us and appears to reverse direction.\n\nVenus governs: love\, beauty\, what we value\, how we relate to others\, aesthetics\, and the things we're attracted to. During Venus retrograde\, these domains come up for internal review — often more intensely than we'd prefer.\n\nThe classic Venus retrograde experiences: an ex reappears (not always because the universe wants you to get back together — sometimes because unfinished emotional business has a deadline). A long-held aesthetic preference shifts. Something you thought you valued turns out to be covering for something deeper. A relationship that seemed settled starts to feel like it needs renegotiation.\n\nVenus is retrograde in Scorpio and Libra — first pressing into depth and intensity (Scorpio)\, then backing into questions of balance\, fairness\, and relational equity (Libra). This is a retrograde that asks: what does love actually look like beneath the presentation of it?\n\nThe philosopher bell hooks defined love not as a feeling but as a practice: 'Love is the will to extend one's self for the purpose of nurturing one's own or another's growth.' Venus retrograde is the annual invitation to measure your relationships against that kind of definition\, rather than the feeling-based version.\n\nWhat relationship in your life — romantic\, creative\, or otherwise — would look different if you brought more honesty to what you actually need from it?\n\nWhat do you value that you've been treating as negotiable — and what would it mean to stop?
CATEGORIES:QUANTUMELODIC,STATION
UID:2d6167bf04c71978367cf2d97efa01b9@quantumelodic.symphony
