SUMMARY:⏰ Saturn Direct →
DESCRIPTION:Saturn stations direct today\, resuming forward motion after its annual retrograde period.\n\nSaturn's station direct is one of the more significant station points of the year — it marks the resumption of forward momentum in the domains Saturn governs: long-term projects\, structural commitments\, accountability\, and the slow building of lasting things.\n\nWhatever was in review during Saturn retrograde (late July through now) has had time to be examined. The structures that needed repair have been assessed. The commitments that needed re-evaluation have been weighed. Saturn direct asks: what did you decide? Now do it.\n\nSaturn in Aries going direct is specifically a signal to take the lessons of the retrograde review and begin implementing them — not gradually or tentatively\, but with the decisive commitment that Aries demands and Saturn's structure provides.\n\nThe philosopher Aristotle distinguished between two kinds of wisdom: sophia (theoretical wisdom\, the knowledge of principles) and phronesis (practical wisdom\, the ability to act rightly in specific situations). Saturn direct is a phronesis moment — the time when knowing must become doing.\n\nWhat have you been figuring out during the past several months that you now need to actually implement?\n\nWhat commitment\, revisited and clarified\, are you ready to honor fully?
CATEGORIES:QUANTUMELODIC,STATION
